[b]MTF Trend Alignment Dashboard[/b] scores trend direction and strength across up to four timeframes using Supertrend and volatility regime classification, combining the results into a single 0–100 confluence score.

[b]What it does[/b]

Instead of switching between timeframes manually, this dashboard evaluates up to four of them in parallel and shows the results side by side. Each timeframe gets a Supertrend direction, a strength score, and a volatility regime label. The overall alignment score reflects how many timeframes agree and how strongly each confirms the direction.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Four timeframes[/b] — Chart timeframe plus three configurable higher timeframes (default 1H / 4H / Daily)
[*][b]Supertrend per TF[/b] — Direction and strength evaluated independently for each timeframe
[*][b]Volatility regime[/b] — Classifies each timeframe as trending, ranging, or transitioning based on ATR behavior
[*][b]Alignment score[/b] — 0–100 confluence score summarizing cross-timeframe agreement
[*][b]Entry quality signals[/b] — Derived from alignment score thresholds to identify high-confluence setups
[/list]

[b]Note:[/b] Requires the RTAFramework library to be published to your TradingView account.

